AGI - Again, as happened last year >, a puppet depicting the president of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, was burned in the evening yesterday, at the end of the 45th edition of the Carnival Liberato of Poggio Mirteto, in the province of Rieti.<br> The puppet of papier-mâché, which in the tradition of the festival created to celebrate the liberation of the medieval village of Poggio Mirteto from the Papal State - and that for this purpose, it takes place on the first Sunday of Lent - is called bammoccio, depicting the features of the premier inside a box of Barbie, with the right arm raised above the inscription 'Fascio di Luce'>.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<br The entire philanthropist traditionally accompanies the puppet towards his incineration, moreover, was dedicated to her and her government. And there was a huge cardboard rocket, ironically dedicated to Elon Musk. Everything, as from tradition, given to the flames late evening<br> Also last year the doll was dedicated to Premier Meloni, and was burned among the polemics of all Italy.
&nbsp;
<div </div
The Carnival of Poggio Mirteto was born after a popular revolt that on February 24, 1861 declared the small village of the province of Rieti free from the Papal State and annexed to the Kingdom of Italy. From here the openly anti-clerical tone of the event, which later, with the signature of the Lateran Pattis, in 1929, was banned from the fascist regime. Only in 1977 an association of the territory resumed to celebrate the event, which then, regarding the organization, passed to the Circolo Arci di Poggio Mirteto, that still today cures the realization of the festival.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Reactions
"To burn a dummy depicting Giorgia Meloni is an ignoble and dangerous act that only nourishes hatred and has no justification. What happened in Poggio Mirteto during the "Carnevale Liberato" is yet another unqualified gesture towards the President of the Council and I hope you will find the firm condemnation of all political forces. In expressing to Giorgia Meloni my sincere closeness, I renew the invitation to lower the tones of political confrontation that never and never must transcend in violence". Ignatius The Russian, President of the Senate of the Republic.&nbsp;
"I express my solidarity with the President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni. It is essential that comparison remain within the limits of mutual respect and civilization, avoiding gestures that may appear as incites to hatred and violence." Thus the president of the Chamber of Deputies, Lorenzo Fontana, in reference to what happened to the "Carnevale Liberato" of Poggio Mirteto, in the province of Rieti.
